# GameManagers Guide

## Manager Responsibilities (one-line each)
- **GridManager** — Central hub. Isometric 2D grid, cell access, coordinate conversion, building placement, bulldozing, sorting order, pathfinding
- **TerrainManager** — Heightmap generation, slope types, prefab selection by slope, cliff stacks (`PlaceCliffWallStack`, serialized face nudges + water-shore Y + `GetMaxCliffSortingOrderFromForegroundWaterNeighbors`)
- **WaterManager** — Water body generation and management (multi-level lakes: **FEAT-37**; **FEAT-37a** / **FEAT-37b** / **FEAT-37c** completed; **FEAT-38** rivers; shore / cliff / water cascades **BUG-42** completed 2026-03-26; **BUG-45** multi-body junctions completed 2026-03-27; **BUG-39** / **BUG-40** completed 2026-03-24; load **BUG-34** / **BUG-35** completed 2026-03-22). Spec: `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` §12–§13
- **ForestManager** — Forest generation (sparse/medium/dense), forestation, deforestation
- **ZoneManager** — RCI zoning (residential, commercial, industrial), zone tile placement
- **RoadManager** — Road drawing, prefab selection by neighbors, road preview
- **InterstateManager** — Interstate highways connecting the map to the exterior
- **GeographyManager** — Orchestrator for all terrain initialization (terrain + water + forest + grid)
- **DemandManager** — R/C/I demand calculation based on population, employment, forests
- **EconomyManager** — Taxes, money, financial transactions
- **CityStats** — Global statistics aggregator: population, employment, water/power capacity
- **EmploymentManager** — Employment and unemployment calculation by zone
- **SimulationManager** — Automatic simulation cycle orchestrator
- **AutoRoadBuilder** — Automatic road network extension
- **AutoZoningManager** — Automatic zoning of cells adjacent to roads
- **AutoResourcePlanner** — Automatic resource building planning
- **GrowthManager** — Zone growth logic
- **GrowthBudgetManager** — Growth budget per category
- **UIManager** — Main UI: popups, toolbar/tool state (`ControlPanel` in `MainScene.unity`), demand bar; UI program: `docs/ui-design-system-project.md`, context `docs/ui-design-system-context.md`, spec `.cursor/specs/ui-design-system.md` (toolbar **§3.3**; layout migration **TECH-07**)
- **CursorManager** — Placement preview, visual cursor
- **TimeManager** — Game speed control, simulation ticks
- **GameNotificationManager** — Singleton. In-game notifications
- **GameSaveManager** — Serialize/deserialize game state
- **GameManager** — Entry point, game loading
- **RegionalMapManager** — Regional map with neighboring cities
- **StatisticsManager** — Historical trend tracking
- **AnimatorManager** (AnimationManager.cs) — Animation control
- **GameDebugInfoBuilder** — Debug text generation for game state

## Helper Services (extracted from managers)
- **GridPathfinder** — A* pathfinding for road routes
- **GridSortingOrderService** — Sorting order computation
- **BuildingPlacementService** — Building placement and load/restore
- **TerraformingService** — Path-level terraform plan computation
- **PathTerraformPlan** — Terraform Apply/Revert, cut-through mode
- **RoadPrefabResolver** — Prefab selection for path and single-cell contexts
- **RoadPathCostConstants** — Shared cost constants for road pathfinding
- **UrbanCentroidService** — Urban centroid and ring metrics for AUTO roads and AUTO zoning (FEAT-32); **keep** — not part of the obsolete proposal system
- **GameBootstrap** — Entry point, game loading flow

## Obsolete / removal backlog
- **`UrbanizationProposalManager`** and related proposal UI — **obsolete**; intentionally **not** run from `SimulationManager.ProcessSimulationTick()`. Do **not** re-enable. Full removal: **TECH-13** in `BACKLOG.md`. **UrbanCentroidService** and ring-based AUTO growth remain supported.

## Rules
- **Road terraform validation:** Use `RoadManager.TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlan` (includes `PathTerraformPlan.TryValidatePhase1Heights`) and `RoadPathValidationContext`. Streets / auto-road should use `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlanLongestValidPrefix` when partial paths are acceptable; interstate uses full-path `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlan` with `forbidCutThrough: true`. Do not use `ComputePathPlan` alone for placement decisions. Spec: `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` §14.
- Every manager is a MonoBehaviour living as a component on a scene GameObject
- NEVER instantiate managers with `new` — they are always scene components
- GridManager is the central hub — all cell operations go through it
- For notifications use `GameNotificationManager.Instance`
- CityStats is the global data aggregator — read city-wide stats from here
